# Working Style

## Before coding
Always:
1. inspect the relevant files
2. identify the actual issue
3. propose a short plan
4. then implement

## For bigger tasks
Work in this order:
1. audit
2. plan
3. shared primitives
4. shell/layout
5. individual page rebuild
6. polish pass

## Never
- never dump huge speculative rewrites
- never change many unrelated files at once
- never claim something is improved without checking it
- never use placeholder text unless requested

## After coding
Always:
- run the relevant build or typecheck command if available
- report what changed
- report any remaining weakness honestly
